---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About" description="Independent software reviews for contractors who need straight answers, not marketing copy.">

<!-- Page Hero -->
<section class="bg-[#0f172a] text-white">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 sm:py-20">
    <p class="text-[#E07A3A] font-semibold text-sm uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">About This Site</p>
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold mb-4" style="font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif; color: white;">About Contractor Software Hub</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-300">Independent software reviews for contractors who need straight answers, not marketing copy.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">

  <section class="mb-12">
    <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-[#1C2B4B] mb-4">Most contractor software reviews are useless.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">They're either written by someone who has never actually run a service business, or they're effectively vendor content — carefully worded to say nothing negative about any product that might be paying an affiliate commission. You end up reading four comparison articles and knowing less than when you started.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">That's what Contractor Software Hub is trying to fix.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">I'm Chris Harper. I started this site after spending more time than I'd like to admit trying to find honest, specific information about contractor software — and consistently coming up empty. What I found instead was a lot of articles that listed the same six tools, described each one's features in language lifted directly from the vendor's own website, and concluded with a recommendation based on nothing.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6" style="font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;">What we actually do here</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">Every review on Contractor Software Hub follows the same process:</p>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="bg-[#f8fafc] border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-5">
        <div class="w-8 h-8 bg-[#E07A3A] text-white rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm mb-3">1</div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-[#1C2B4B] mb-2">We sign up for trials</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Or go deep enough on demos, pricing pages, and documentation to understand the real capabilities — not just the marketing copy.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-[#f8fafc] border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-5">
        <div class="w-8 h-8 bg-[#E07A3A] text-white rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm mb-3">2</div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-[#1C2B4B] mb-2">We read hundreds of reviews</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Filtering G2 and Capterra feedback for patterns from real contractors, not paid promoters or one-time users with an axe to grind.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-[#f8fafc] border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-5">
        <div class="w-8 h-8 bg-[#E07A3A] text-white rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm mb-3">3</div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-[#1C2B4B] mb-2">We analyze pricing honestly</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Including the hidden fees, tier restrictions, and contract terms vendors don't put in their pricing page headline.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-[#f8fafc] border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-5">
        <div class="w-8 h-8 bg-[#E07A3A] text-white rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm mb-3">4</div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-[#1C2B4B] mb-2">We say who it's wrong for</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Every review includes a clear "not for" section so you can disqualify tools that don't fit your operation.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;">How we make money</h2>
    <div class="border-l-4 border-[#E07A3A] pl-5 bg-amber-50 py-4 pr-4 rounded-r-lg mb-4">
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Contractor Software Hub earns affiliate commissions when you click through to a software product and sign up. That's disclosed on every article and on our <a href="/affiliate-disclosure/" class="text-[#1C2B4B] underline hover:text-[#E07A3A] font-medium">affiliate disclosure page</a>.</p>
    </div>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">This means we have a financial incentive to be helpful enough that you trust the recommendation — because if the reviews aren't useful, you don't click, and the whole thing falls apart. A bad tool gets a critical review here, regardless of commission rates.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;">Who this is for</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Painting contractors, electricians, plumbers, HVAC technicians, roofers, landscapers, general contractors — anyone running a real service business who needs to choose software without sitting through six vendor demos to get a straight answer.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">We write for contractors running 1–50 people. If you're a 500-person enterprise evaluating ServiceTitan at the executive level, this isn't the site for you. If you're a 12-person plumbing company trying to figure out if Jobber is worth the money, it is.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8 bg-[#1C2B4B] rounded-xl p-6 text-white">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2" style="font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif; color: white;">Get in touch</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">Questions, corrections, or a tool you think we should cover? Use the <a href="/contact/" class="text-[#E07A3A] hover:underline font-medium">contact page</a>. If you've used a tool we haven't reviewed, or you think we got something wrong, say so.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">— Chris Harper | ContractorSoftwareHub.com</p>
  </section>

</main>

</Layout>
